data.title: 20000 series: Part 2)
data.text:
Pacific Jazz 10000/20000 series discography

World Pacific released a series of albums on the Pacific Jazz label between 1960 and 1970. Early albums in the series were probably numbered PJ 1 to PJ 90..(ish) for mono and PJS 1 to PJS 90..(ish) for stereo. When the series reached catalog numbers in the 90s the numbering used was changed. Mono releases were numbered with a 10000 number and stereo with a 20000 number. For example instead of PJ 99 and PJS 99 the release was numbered PJ 10099 and PJS 20099. From some point in 1967 onward only stereo versions were released.

The discography is divided into 2 pages. The current page lists LPs in the sequence 10100 to 10176. These were released in the 1965-1970 period. When available the "See more details" link leads to a page with a track list and musicians information.

Pacific Jazz pages on the site

10000/20000 series : Pacific Jazz 1 - 10099 | Pacific Jazz 10100 - 10176

Plays and Sings, Chet Baker, 1968, Pacific Jazz 20138

Tracks : But Not For Me, Happy Little Sunbeam, Look For The Silver Lining, Tenderly, I Get Along Very Well Without You, There's A Small Hotel, Summertime, There Will Never Be Another You, Bea's Flat, I Fall In Love Too Easily, My Funny Valentine, My Buddy

Tracks from sessions recorded between 1953 and 1956.

The Genius Of Gerry Mulligan, Gerry Mulligan, 1968, Pacific Jazz 20140

Tracks : Get Happy, She Didn't Say Yes, Bernie's Tune, Darn That Dream, Five Brothers, I Can't Believe That You're In Love With Me, Gold Rush, Blues For Tiny, Polka Dots And Moonbeams, Blue At The Roots, The Lady's In Love With You

Recordings from sessions in the 1952 to 1954 period. Originally released on Pacific Jazz in 1960.

Konitz Meets Mulligan, Lee Konitz & Gerry Mulligan, 1968, Pacific Jazz 20142

Tracks : I Can't Believe That You're In Love With Me, Broadway, Almost Like Being In Love, Sextet, Oh, Lady Be Good, Too Marvelous For Words, Lover Man, I'll Remember April, These Foolish Things, All The Things You Are

Musicians : Lee Konitz, Gerry Mulligan, Chet Baker, Carson Smith, Joe Mondragon, Larry Bunker

Originally released on World Pacific as Lee Konitz Plays With The Gerry Mulligan Quartet. Released by Pacific Jazz as Konitz Meets Mulligan in 1962.

This Is The Blues Vol 2, Various Artists, 1969, Pacific Jazz 20150

Tracks : I Feel All Right (Long Gone Miles), How Long Have It Been Since You Been Home (Lightnin' Hopkins), Baby Please Don't Go (Brownie McGhee & Sonny Terry), Puppy Love (Bumble Bee Slim), Barefoot Rock (Long Gone Miles), If You Steal My Chickens You Can't Make 'Em Lay (Lightnin' Hopkins, Brownie McGhee, Sonny Terry And Big Joe Williams), How Long Blues (Barbara Dane), Wake Up In The Mornin' (Bumble Bee Slim), Livin' With The Blues (Brownie McGhee & Sonny Terry), Long Gone (Long Gone Miles)
